The paper proposes a new neural architecture for reading comprehension, which is a task in natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves attention mechanisms and dense connections, which are common in deep learning and neural network research, suggesting that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper uses convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and bidirectional LSTMs (BLSTMs) for feature extraction, which are common in computer vision (CV) and NLP research, respectively, indicating that cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are also possible sub-categories.
